{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01No4Rgtx9tPmXDdjG5H3rxD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"Step2 kernel: pressure, viscosity, and XSPH force computation.\n     2→\n     3→Compiles physics/kernels/step2.cu via CuPy RawModule and provides\n     4→functions to upload GranularParams to constant memory and launch\n     5→the K_Step2 kernel.\n     6→\n     7→Uses shared constant memory from common.cuh:\n     8→  c_grid     -- GridParams (uploaded by hash_sort.py)\n     9→  c_sim      -- SimParams (uploaded by step1.py)\n    10→  c_precalc  -- PrecalcParams (uploaded by step1.py)\n    11→  c_materials -- MaterialProps[32] (uploaded by materials.py)\n    12→\n    13→Additional constant memory local to this module:\n    14→  c_granular -- GranularParams (mu(I) rheology + xsph_epsilon)\n    15→\n    16→Tait EOS pressure\n    17→-----------------\n    18→- FLUID/GRANULAR: p_raw = k * (pow(rho/rho0, 7) - 1)\n    19→  - FLUID:    p = max(p_raw, -0.5*k)\n    20→  - GRANULAR: p = max(p_raw, 0)\n    21→- GAS: p = k_gas * max(rho - rho0, 0) with gamma=1\n    22→\n    23→Force accumulation\n    24→------------------\n    25→- Pressure force: pressure_precalc * m_j * (p_i/rho_i^2 + p_j/rho_j^2) * grad_spiky_variable\n    26→- Viscosity force: viscosity_precalc * m_j * (v_j - v_i) / rho_j * lap_visc_variable\n    27→- XSPH (FLUID only): epsilon * sum(m_j / rho_avg * (v_j - v_i) * W_poly6)\n    28→\"\"\"\n    29→\n    30→from __future__ import annotations\n    31→\n    32→import os\n    33→from typing import Optional\n    34→\n    35→import cupy\n    36→import numpy as np\n    37→\n    38→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    39→# Default physical parameters\n    40→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    41→\n    42→DEFAULT_MU_S = np.float32(0.36)\n    43→DEFAULT_MU_2 = np.float32(0.70)\n    44→DEFAULT_I0 = np.float32(0.3)\n    45→DEFAULT_MU_MAX = np.float32(10000.0)\n    46→DEFAULT_PARTICLE_SPACING = np.float32(0.02)\n    47→DEFAULT_MU0 = np.float32(3.5)\n    48→DEFAULT_XSPH_EPSILON = np.float32(0.5)\n    49→\n    50→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"374499ef-5ec0-4577-85fa-be8b5d7ef994","uuid":"3ca4bb69-0553-4a00-a6f7-42b41bf5ab4d","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/step2.py","content":"\"\"\"Step2 kernel: pressure, viscosity, and XSPH force computation.\n\nCompiles physics/kernels/step2.cu via CuPy RawModule and provides\nfunctions to upload GranularParams to constant memory and launch\nthe K_Step2 kernel.\n\nUses shared constant memory from common.cuh:\n  c_grid     -- GridParams (uploaded by hash_sort.py)\n  c_sim      -- SimParams (uploaded by step1.py)\n  c_precalc  -- PrecalcParams (uploaded by step1.py)\n  c_materials -- MaterialProps[32] (uploaded by materials.py)\n\nAdditional constant memory local to this module:\n  c_granular -- GranularParams (mu(I) rheology + xsph_epsilon)\n\nTait EOS pressure\n-----------------\n- FLUID/GRANULAR: p_raw = k * (pow(rho/rho0, 7) - 1)\n  - FLUID:    p = max(p_raw, -0.5*k)\n  - GRANULAR: p = max(p_raw, 0)\n- GAS: p = k_gas * max(rho - rho0, 0) with gamma=1\n\nForce accumulation\n------------------\n- Pressure force: pressure_precalc * m_j * (p_i/rho_i^2 + p_j/rho_j^2) * grad_spiky_variable\n- Viscosity force: viscosity_precalc * m_j * (v_j - v_i) / rho_j * lap_visc_variable\n- XSPH (FLUID only): epsilon * sum(m_j / rho_avg * (v_j - v_i) * W_poly6)\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport os\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nimport cupy\nimport numpy as np\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Default physical parameters\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\nDEFAULT_MU_S = np.float32(0.36)\nDEFAULT_MU_2 = np.float32(0.70)\nDEFAULT_I0 = np.float32(0.3)\nDEFAULT_MU_MAX = np.float32(10000.0)\nDEFAULT_PARTICLE_SPACING = np.float32(0.02)\nDEFAULT_MU0 = np.float32(3.5)\nDEFAULT_XSPH_EPSILON = np.float32(0.5)\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------","numLines":50,"startLine":1,"totalLines":280}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019p21X18MiRkAruAgpZD5yZ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"Integrate kernel: symplectic Euler with SDF boundaries and color update.\n     2→\n     3→Compiles physics/kernels/integrate.cu via CuPy RawModule and provides\n     4→a function to launch K_Integrate which performs:\n     5→  - Symplectic Euler velocity/position integration\n     6→  - Impulse-style SDF box boundary collisions (restitution + Coulomb friction)\n     7→  - GAS buoyancy and drag\n     8→  - Velocity magnitude clamping\n     9→  - Particle color computation from material, temperature, and health\n    10→  - Writeback to UNSORTED arrays via sort_indexes permutation\n    11→\n    12→Uses shared constant memory from common.cuh:\n    13→  c_sim       -- SimParams (gravity, dt, restitution, wall_friction, world bounds)\n    14→  c_materials -- MaterialProps[32] (for color lookup)\n    15→\"\"\"\n    16→\n    17→from __future__ import annotations\n    18→\n    19→import os\n    20→from typing import Optional\n    21→\n    22→import cupy\n    23→import numpy as np\n    24→\n    25→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    26→# CuPy RawModule compilation\n    27→# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n    28→\n    29→_module: Optional[object] = None\n    30→\n    31→\n    32→def _ensure_ptx_if_needed() -> None:\n    33→    \"\"\"Force PTX compilation when GPU arch exceeds NVRTC's max sm target.\"\"\"\n    34→    from cupy.cuda import compiler as _compiler\n    35→    from cupy.cuda import device as _device\n    36→\n    37→    gpu_cc = _device.Device().compute_capability\n    38→    nvrtc_max = _compiler._get_max_compute_capability()\n    39→    if int(gpu_cc) > int(nvrtc_max):\n    40→        _compiler._use_ptx = True\n    41→        if hasattr(_compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc, \"_cache\"):\n    42→            _compiler._get_arch_for_options_for_nvrtc._cache = {}\n    43→        if hasattr(_compiler._get_arch, \"_cache\"):\n    44→            _compiler._get_arch._cache = {}\n    45→\n    46→\n    47→def _get_module() -> \"object\":\n    48→    \"\"\"Compile (or return cached) CuPy RawModule from integrate.cu.\"\"\"\n    49→    global _module\n    50→    if _module is not None:\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"374499ef-5ec0-4577-85fa-be8b5d7ef994","uuid":"03cd5a27-5a02-4dc9-96e4-e0c1208227ba","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/c/WORK/gpusphsim/fallingsand3d/integrate.py","content":"\"\"\"Integrate kernel: symplectic Euler with SDF boundaries and color update.\n\nCompiles physics/kernels/integrate.cu via CuPy RawModule and provides\na function to launch K_Integrate which performs:\n  - Symplectic Euler velocity/position integration\n  - Impulse-style SDF box boundary collisions (restitution + Coulomb friction)\n  - GAS buoyancy and drag\n  - Velocity magnitude clamping\n  - Particle color computation from material, temperature, and health\n  - Writeback to UNSORTED arrays via sort_indexes permutation\n\nUses shared constant memory from common.cuh:\n  c_sim       -- SimParams (gravity, dt, restitution, wall_friction, world bounds)\n  c_materials -- MaterialProps[32] (for color lookup)\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport os\nfrom typing import Optional\n\nimport cupy\nimport numpy as np\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# CuPy RawModule compilation\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n_module: Optional[object] = None