{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EsG6xjU1aweX6B7ttmMHhN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The viscous CFL is incredibly tight (6.4e-8 s) with rho_min=0.2 (fire). This would make the simulation nearly unusable because dt_viscous dominates. The issue is that fire has rho=0.2 and mu_max=10000 applies to GRANULAR, but GAS particles don't use mu(I). Let me fix the viscosity bounds calculation to be more realistic:\n\nThe `_compute_viscosity_bounds` should use mu_max only when computing eta for GRANULAR. And rho_min for viscous CFL should only consider materials that actually have high viscosity. Let me rethink this.\n\nLooking at the acceptance criteria more carefully: `dt_viscous = accuracy * rho_min * h^2 / max(max_eta, 1e-6)` — this is the global viscous CFL. The issue is that rho_min should be the minimum density of materials that can actually have high eta. GAS materials never run mu(I), so rho_min shouldn't include gas densities when computing the granular viscous CFL.\n\nActually, looking at the notes: \"Viscous CFL with mu_max=10000: dt_visc ~ 6.4e-5s\" - let me verify that number. They must be using rho_min for a non-gas material."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":819,"cache_read_input_tokens":106556,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":819},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"374499ef-5ec0-4577-85fa-be8b5d7ef994","uuid":"4d0297fd-80ff-49bc-ac29-f590702f0d4e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01EsG6xjU1aweX6B7ttmMHhN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01D2DGHkAD9eabHhbe1HpX16","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\n# From the notes: dt_visc ~ 6.4e-5s\n# dt_visc = accuracy * rho_min * h^2 / max_eta\n# With accuracy=0.4, h=0.04, max_eta=10000\n# We need rho_min such that: 0.4 * rho_min * 0.0016 / 10000 = 6.4e-5\n# rho_min = 6.4e-5 * 10000 / (0.4 * 0.0016) = 1000\n# So rho_min=1000 (water) not rho_min=0.2 (fire)\n\n# If rho_min is the min non-gas density = 800 (OIL)\ndt_visc = 0.4 * 800 * 0.04**2 / 10000\nprint(f'dt_visc (rho_min=800 OIL) = {dt_visc:.6f}')\n\n# If rho_min=1000 (water)\ndt_visc = 0.4 * 1000 * 0.04**2 / 10000\nprint(f'dt_visc (rho_min=1000 WATER) = {dt_visc:.6f}')\n\n# If rho_min = minimum of all non-DEAD, non-STATIC, non-GAS materials\n# That would be OIL at 800, or WOOD at 600 (but WOOD is STATIC)\n# Non-STATIC, non-GAS: SAND=1600, DIRT=1500, GRAVEL=1800, WATER=1000, OIL=800, LAVA=2500, ACID=1200, GUNPOWDER=1700\n# Min is OIL=800\ndt_visc = 0.4 * 800 * 0.04**2 / 10000\nprint(f'Min non-gas/non-static rho = 800 (OIL), dt_visc = {dt_visc:.6f}')\n\"\n","description":"Verify viscous CFL calculation"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":819,"cache_read_input_tokens":106556,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":819},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"374499ef-5ec0-4577-85fa-be8b5d7ef994","uuid":"f978bedf-4dfe-4d18-837c-c92c6b871d59"}
