{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_017Tz2bEhYQ2c2n5EXG6sksH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Commit successful. Here's a summary of what was implemented for US-025:\n\n## US-025 - Adaptive Timestep with CFL Condition\n\n### Changes\n\n**`fallingsand3d/simulation.py`** (major changes):\n- Added `accuracy` parameter (CFL number, 0.1-1.0, default 0.4) and `fixed_dt` toggle (default OFF)\n- `_compute_c_sound()` — precomputes acoustic speed from material table: max(sqrt(k*gamma/rho0))\n- `_compute_viscosity_bounds()` — precomputes max_eta (mu_max=10000 for GRANULAR) and rho_min (excluding GAS)\n- `_compute_adaptive_dt(n)` — per-frame CFL computation:\n  - `dt_advection = accuracy * h / max(max_v, 1e-6)` via CuPy max velocity reduction\n  - `dt_acoustic = 0.25 * h / c_sound`\n  - `dt_viscous = accuracy * rho_min * h^2 / max(max_eta, 1e-6)`\n  - `dt = min(all three)` clamped to [1e-5, 0.005]\n- `_upload_dt()` — re-uploads c_sim with new dt to all 5 modules that read it\n- `adjust_accuracy()`, `toggle_fixed_dt()` control methods\n\n**`fallingsand3d/main.py`** (minor changes):\n- `[`/`]` keys adjust accuracy by ±0.1\n- `F` key toggles fixed/adaptive dt\n- Window title now shows dt (ms) and accuracy\n\n### Key design decisions\n- No kernel (.cu) changes needed — all kernels already read dt from `c_sim` constant memory\n- Acoustic speed and viscosity bounds precomputed at init (material table doesn't change)\n- Adaptive dt computed once per render frame, not per substep (avoids CuPy reduction overhead in tight loop)\n- rho_min for viscous CFL excludes GAS materials (they never use mu(I))\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":325,"cache_read_input_tokens":116833,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":325},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"